{
  "doc_id": "50719",
  "text": "Twisted K-theory resurfaced in the late 1990's with Witten's work on classification of D-branes charges in type II string theory [52] . Fruitful interactions between algebraic topology and physics afforded by twisted K-theory continues today, see e.g. [1] , [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] and [CITATION_4] . The work of Freed, Hopkins and Teleman [CITATION_5] relates the twisted equivariant K-theory of a compact Lie group G to the \"Verlinde ring\" of its loop group. For a recent survey of twisted K-theory we refer to [CITATION_6] .",
